Thank you @goodtrouble :
Thank you to the creators, cast, and crew.. The passion, love, and laughs made this experience so joyful and worth every long hour day.

Malika & Isaac: thank you for showing me a passion and devotion to one another. The human experience with flaws and love. This is the character I spent the most time with, so this is bittersweet to say goodbye. The character I relate to the most.. Isaac’s warm heart was a pleasure to portray. Very grateful I was able to show what I can do emotionally and intentionally with this man. 

@zuriadele thank you for keeping our space safe. The chemistry and respect we have for one another made this ride amazing and filled with love. I never had to worry about anything with you. An honest person which is something I cherish very much even more the older I get. You are a light. You are a gift. Love you! 💙💙

Even though this is the last season, watch the rest of season 5 come January! Give us a proper goodbye! 🙏🏽🤞🏽

I’m always hungry for progression. I’ve had an inconsistent journey with my body for years due to a back injury. As a former athlete, most my life my identity was tied with my physical body. When that has been taken from me at times, my mental health was too. Took me to a negative space to not be able sit in a car without feeling extreme pain. I’m so grateful to be in the space I’m in now. From squatting (kinda lol) 315 lbs, to boxing, hoopin, playing with my daughter and God kids.. So much to be thankful for. I had to take accountability (which is scary for most) and decide to take control of my mental health and physical health. If you are in a place you are not happy in, YOU have more power then you give yourself credit for. Your mind is your strongest tool and you can get on the path you want. Prioritizing my mental is what allowed me to get physically healthy and set my routines and diet. Outside opinions of others mean NOTHING. If people are lying and putting THEIR limitations on you, that is THEIR issue and not YOURS. You are what you attach to I am (Confucius). 

S/O to @liftsociety for providing a space for me to maintain my mind and body 🙏🏽💪🏽

And to @q24training and @craigliebenson for getting me on the right track 💙🫡
